###Step 2: Substitute the known point into linear equation

The parallel line will have a slope of $\purpleC{-0.75}$ and pass through the point $\redD{(8,0)}$.  Let's start from the point-slope form of the equation of the parallel line, then solve for $y$.  [[☃ explanation 1]]

>$\begin{align}
y-\redD{0} &= \purpleC{-0.75}(x-\redD{8})\\\\\\
y &= \purpleC{-0.75}x \greenD{+6}
\end{align}$
